blished on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 21:49:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/utah-man-killed-biden-visit-assassination-threat" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/09/former-ireland-rugby-star-ronan-ogara-turns-the-air-bleu" target="_blank">Former rugby star’s Irish-accented French team talk hailed as ‘absolutely glorious’</a></h2><div class="description"> La Rochelle coach Ronan O’Gara blends French with English swearing with a few choice words. Former Ireland international O'Gara is a former Ireland international who coaches the French side. The pep talk was graced with a Cork accent, graced by a former Irish international.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:02:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/09/former-ireland-rugby-star-ronan-ogara-turns-the-air-bleu" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/mines-drone-strikes-organised-plan-to-export-ukraine-grain-via-danube-ports-is-no-easy-fix" target="_blank">Turning food into a weapon: how Russia resorted to one of the oldest forms of warfare</a></h2><div class="description"> With Russia blockading Ukraine’s eastern ports, an alternative route to the west is possible but faces serious problems. Moscow pulled out of an UN-brokered deal to allow Ukrainian grain exports through the Black Sea last month. The mining of the Kakhovka dam in June threatens to turn southern Ukrainian farmland into a dustbowl.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:47:24 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/mines-drone-strikes-organised-plan-to-export-ukraine-grain-via-danube-ports-is-no-easy-fix" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/ukrainian-force-cross-dnipro-river-bid-breach-southern-frontline-kherson-city" target="_blank">Ukrainian forces cross Dnipro River in bid to breach southern frontline</a></h2><div class="description"> Up to seven boats landed east of Kherson city and broke through defensive lines, say Russian military bloggers. Ukrainian forces have made an attempt to cross the Dnipro River dividing liberated and occupied Kheron. The river has for months served as the frontline in the south of Ukraine.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:11:06 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/ukrainian-force-cross-dnipro-river-bid-breach-southern-frontline-kherson-city" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/germany-arranges-supply-of-30-leopard-1-tanks-for-ukraine" target="_blank">Germany arranges supply of 30 Leopard 1 tanks for Ukraine</a></h2><div class="description"> Arms firm Rheinmetall to refurbish vehicles following military aid package announced at Nato summit. Some of the vehicles are reportedly in such poor condition they will serve only for spare parts. The tanks are part of a fleet of 49 vehicles that the Düsseldorf-based company purchased from the Belgian private defence company OIP Land Systems.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 15:53:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/germany-arranges-supply-of-30-leopard-1-tanks-for-ukraine" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/russia-ukraine-war-at-a-glance-what-we-know-on-day-533-of-the-invasion" target="_blank">Russia-Ukraine war at a glance: what we know on day 533 of the invasion</a></h2><div class="description"> One dead and eight unaccounted for in explosion at factory near Moscow that used to supply Russian military. Ukrainian forces launch raid across Dnipro river that serves as frontline in southern Ukraine. Up to seven boats land near settlement of Kozachi Laheri, east of Kherson city, and break through Russian defensive lines.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 23:54:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/russia-ukraine-war-at-a-glance-what-we-know-on-day-533-of-the-invasion" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/09/cross-border-kayaking-balkans-montenegro-albania" target="_blank">‘The police wave us off like old friends’: cross-border kayaking from Montenegro to Albania</a></h2><div class="description"> A six-day water-borne adventure takes paddlers through the Balkans to the Adriatic coast. Starting in Lake Skadar (Liqeni i Shkodrës), it spans both countries and is the largest lake on the Balkan peninsula. With a mix of wild camping, homestays and waterfront cabins, it’s the kesti.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 09:08:58 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/09/cross-border-kayaking-balkans-montenegro-albania" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/10/its-really-only-the-beginning-are-we-on-the-cusp-of-a-breakthrough-in-endometriosis" target="_blank">‘It’s really only the beginning’: are we on the cusp of a breakthrough in endometriosis?</a></h2><div class="description"> After generations of inaction, researchers and activists are hopeful a new path is being charted in understanding and treating the crippling chronic condition. ‘There’s an excitement at the moment,’ says Andrew Horne, a professor of gynaecology and reproductive sciences at the University of Edinburgh.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 15:00:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/10/its-really-only-the-beginning-are-we-on-the-cusp-of-a-breakthrough-in-endometriosis" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/no-swearing-no-singing-no-fancy-dress-uks-strictest-pub-calls-time" target="_blank">No swearing, no singing, no fancy dress: UK’s ‘strictest pub’ calls time</a></h2><div class="description"> Landlord Shaun Collinge has run the York pub for 31 years and says the rules are harder to enforce post-pandemic. Rules include: no swearing, no singing, no television, no music, no stag parties, no hen dos and no fancy dress.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 12:55:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/no-swearing-no-singing-no-fancy-dress-uks-strictest-pub-calls-time" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/09/secret-restaurant-costs-is-it-outrageous-to-charge-2-to-cut-a-sandwich-in-half" target="_blank">Secret restaurant costs: is it outrageous to charge €2 to cut a sandwich in half?</a></h2><div class="description"> A tourist in a cafe in Lake Como, Italy, has been charged €2 for having his sandwich cut in half. He wanted to share the sandwich with his girlfriend, but when the bill arrived it listed the price of €2. A snapshot of the receipt went viral, prompting Italian newspapers to question the owner of the cafe.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 15:40:29 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/09/secret-restaurant-costs-is-it-outrageous-to-charge-2-to-cut-a-sandwich-in-half" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/games/2023/aug/09/pushing-buttons-disney-star-wars-hotel-florida--galactic-starcruiser" target="_blank">Pushing Buttons: Why the closure of Disney’s Star Wars hotel isn’t the end of immersive gaming</a></h2><div class="description"> The $350 million Galactic Starcruiser will shut this year, less than two years after opening. The immersive immersive Star Wars hotel in Florida will shut down next month. The hotel is best known for being horrendously expensive – $4,809 for a couple for two nights, or $1,500 a person if you fit four to a cabin.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 14:00:27 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/games/2023/aug/09/pushing-buttons-disney-star-wars-hotel-florida--galactic-starcruiser" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/hiking-relationships-family-dating" target="_blank">What I learned from hiking with a partner who strode ahead – and wouldn’t slow down</a></h2><div class="description"> In our 20s, we’d trekked for three months in Nepal, only stopping to sip hot chai and eat warm dal for meals. After serving in the Peace Corps in the Central African Republic, I'd anticipated a romantic journey as a couple with my best friend turned boyfriend. But as hiking partners, we were rarely together.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 11:00:24 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/hiking-relationships-family-dating" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/09/deplorable-places-why-one-bbc-drama-is-shedding-light-on-irelands-church-run-abuse-factories" target="_blank">‘Deplorable places’: why one BBC drama is shedding light on Ireland’s church-run abuse factories</a></h2><div class="description"> Joe Murtagh wrote new thriller The Woman in the Wall, starring Ruth Wilson. The Bafta nominee learned about the Magdalene Laundries, he said he had to tell their tale. Here, he explains how he wrote the thriller to tell the tale of the women sent to the laundries.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 14:29:07 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/09/deplorable-places-why-one-bbc-drama-is-shedding-light-on-irelands-church-run-abuse-factories" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/aug/09/mushroom-mystery-family-lunch-leaves-australian-town-reeling-after-three-die-in-suspected-poisoning" target="_blank">Mushroom mystery: family lunch leaves Australian town reeling after three deaths in suspected poisoning</a></h2><div class="description"> Police investigating what looks like a fatal case of food poisoning in Leongatha in eastern Victoria. Locals recall the victims as kind and community-spirited. Four of the guests began feeling very unwell and eventually sought treatment at local hospitals. Police are investigating what appears to be a fatal food poisoning.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 12:02:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/aug/09/mushroom-mystery-family-lunch-leaves-australian-town-reeling-after-three-die-in-suspected-poisoning" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/lee-anderson-migrant-politics-margaret-thatcher-rishi-sunak" target="_blank">Lee Anderson’s vile anti-migrant comments pose this question: do we want politics like this? | Hugh Muir</a></h2><div class="description"> Lee Anderson, the deputy chair of the Conservative party, said asylum seekers should 'f*** off back to France' He was speaking to the Daily Express, with the knowledge that this once-great British newspaper now thrives on printing such things. Even Thatcher’s governments were above the hateful, toxic rhetoric now being favoured by Sunak and his lieutenants.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 12:21:20 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/lee-anderson-migrant-politics-margaret-thatcher-rishi-sunak" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/picture/2023/aug/09/steve-bell-on-lee-anderson-and-the-bibby-stockholm-barge-cartoon" target="_blank">Steve Bell on Lee Anderson and the Bibby Stockholm barge – cartoon</a></h2><div class="description"> CNN.com will feature iReporter photos in a weekly Travel Snapshots gallery. Please submit your best shots for next week's gallery of iReporters. Visit CNN iReport.com/Travel next Wednesday for a new gallery of snapshots of the world's most beautiful beaches.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 18:39:52 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/picture/2023/aug/09/steve-bell-on-lee-anderson-and-the-bibby-stockholm-barge-cartoon" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/the-strange-tale-of-the-crooked-house-tells-a-much-bigger-story" target="_blank">The strange tale of The Crooked House tells a much bigger story</a></h2><div class="description"> The Crooked House always lived large in the imagination of anyone from the West Midlands. It was the pub where things – marbles, coins, even people – rolled uphill. The first time you heard the words ‘optical’ and ‘illusion’ used together was in relation to the mysteries of the pub. Adrian Chiles is a broadcaster, writer and Guardian columnist.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 16:01:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/the-strange-tale-of-the-crooked-house-tells-a-much-bigger-story" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/donald-trump-prison-cell-campaign-for-us-president" target="_blank">Perverse as it sounds, Donald Trump in a prison cell may be the worst possible outcome | Emma Brockes</a></h2><div class="description"> Imagine Trump posing as the ultimate martyr, campaigning for president from jail – his supporters would find it irresistible. Trump is front and centre every day, but in danger of ascending to a new position in the news cycle: 'The ultimate martyr' He was still there, obviously, wandering the corridors at Mar-a-Lago and posting screeds.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 15:08:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/donald-trump-prison-cell-campaign-for-us-president" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/narendra-modi-bjp-india-manipur-violence" target="_blank">Narendra Modi has ignored religious violence for too long. Now he must face the music | Priya Sharma</a></h2><div class="description"> Narendra Modi is accused of turning a blind eye to three months of bloodshed in some of the poorest villages of India. Hundreds of villages destroyed, Christian churches and schools torched, and widespread sexual assault of women. About 50,000 people have fled their homes; at least 124 are dead.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 16:24:02 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/narendra-modi-bjp-india-manipur-violence" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/immersive-van-gogh-art-disney-lighthouse" target="_blank">So long ‘immersive Van Gogh’: we deserve better than this cynical and elitist approach to art | Rachel Connolly</a></h2><div class="description"> Disney’s Lighthouse Immersive puts on shows in which reproductions of work by household-name artists are blown up and projected on to the walls of galleries. Music is piped into the space to curate the mood, taking the place that imagination plays in a traditional exhibition. We never needed gizmos and expensive tickets to enjoy great art.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 13:26:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/immersive-van-gogh-art-disney-lighthouse" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/labour-win-power-party-strategy-ideas" target="_blank">This narrow, win-at-all-costs strategy could take Labour to victory, but not to power |  Neal Lawson</a></h2><div class="description"> Neal Lawson is director of the cross-party campaign organisation Compass. He knows that without bold, transformative ideas, success will simply tie the party’s hands. He says the plan was not to win but to snatch the party back under the temporary cloak of Corbynism-without-Corbyn.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 11:05:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/labour-win-power-party-strategy-ideas" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/female-andrew-tate-influencer-dating-debt-man-bills" target="_blank">‘The female Andrew Tate’: the new influencer dating doctrine is extreme – but I can see why it’s popular | Kimberly McIntosh</a></h2><div class="description"> Young women struggling with debt and burnout need a better vision than getting a rich man to pay the bills. The way to get wealthy men to buy you drinks is to go to high-end bars alone before the after-work rush. SheraSeven, the self-styled ‘financial adviser’ whose advice I had inadvertently followed, says Shera.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 09:00:21 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/female-andrew-tate-influencer-dating-debt-man-bills" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/the-guardian-view-on-the-electoral-commission-hack-democracy-needs-stronger-safeguards" target="_blank">The Guardian view on the electoral commission hack: democracy needs stronger safeguards | Editorial</a></h2><div class="description"> A culture of complacency around data security and a government obsessed with partisan games have put electoral regulation at risk. The security breach was only discovered last October and made public this week. The perpetrators have been identified as “hostile actors” which could be a criminal gang, a foreign state, or the former acting on behalf of the latter.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:34:09 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/the-guardian-view-on-the-electoral-commission-hack-democracy-needs-stronger-safeguards" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/the-guardian-view-on-the-amazon-summit-rich-nations-must-now-step-up" target="_blank">The Guardian view on the Amazon summit: rich nations must now step up</a></h2><div class="description"> Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva defeated Jair Bolsonaro by a margin of 1.8% in last October's election. The Amazon rainforest was hurtling towards a tipping point after which it would no longer function as a climate stabiliser. Deforestation dropped by 42% during Lula’s first seven months in office, and the state has returned as a protective state.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:34:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2023/aug/09/the-guardian-view-on-the-amazon-summit-rich-nations-must-now-step-up" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/lee-anderson-ugly-words-shame-britain" target="_blank">Lee Anderson’s ugly words shame Britain | Letters</a></h2><div class="description"> Alexandra Wright joined a march of silence from the library in Ladbroke Grove to Grenfell Tower. The Tory deputy chair used demeaning and disgusting language in his remarks about asylum seekers, she says. Plus letters from Kevin Potter and Will King, from Will King and Alexandra Wright.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:28:54 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/lee-anderson-ugly-words-shame-britain" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/09/views-from-both-sides-of-the-digital-divide" target="_blank">Views from both sides of the digital divide | Letters</a></h2><div class="description"> Josephine Culhane was nodding vigorously in agreement when she read your editorial. An hour later she was having a conversation with your subscription team about the fact that I could no longer have my subscription vouchers for the Guardian. I now need to use a barcode that would be scanned by my newsagent – in our only village shop. They do not have a scanner.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:28:49 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/09/views-from-both-sides-of-the-digital-divide" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/womens-world-cup-2023-last-16-power-rankings-england-france-australia-usa" target="_blank">Women’s World Cup power rankings: France on the rise, England drop down</a></h2><div class="description"> Japan continue to look the most in-form team in the competition. France, Australia, Spain and Colombia are all making upward moves. Hinata Miyazawa remains top scorer with five goals, equalling Homare Sawa’s Golden Boot-winning total in 2011.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 12:19:45 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/womens-world-cup-2023-last-16-power-rankings-england-france-australia-usa" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/lucy-bronze-england-unhappy-performances-womens-world-cup-colombia" target="_blank">Lucy Bronze admits England unhappy with performances and ‘can give more’</a></h2><div class="description"> England face Colombia in the World Cup quarter-final on Saturday. Lucy Bronze says England are 'not happy' with their performances. The Lionesses laboured against Nigeria, losing Lauren James to a red card for stepping on Michelle Alozie. It was the third time in four games that England have looked unconvincing.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 11:00:02 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/lucy-bronze-england-unhappy-performances-womens-world-cup-colombia" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/womens-world-cup-2023-france-vs-australia-squad-best-players-wendie-renard-kadidiatou-diani-vicki-becho-eugenie-le-sommer" target="_blank">Four France players who can break Australian hearts at the World Cup | Jack Snape</a></h2><div class="description"> Matildas take on France in World Cup quarter-final in Brisbane on Saturday. France started the tournament slowly before beating Brazil 2-1 and Panama 6-3. Since then, the world No 5-ranked side have been on a long journey. Sam Kerr's injury saga, Sam Kerr’s dour early victory over Ireland, defensive frailties against Nigeria, then the Matildaas’ revival.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 15:00:30 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/womens-world-cup-2023-france-vs-australia-squad-best-players-wendie-renard-kadidiatou-diani-vicki-becho-eugenie-le-sommer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/the-premier-league-is-back-for-an-uncluttered-if-uncertain-new-season" target="_blank">The Premier League is back for an uncluttered, if uncertain, new season | Barney Ronay</a></h2><div class="description"> A strange brew of noises off haunts the coming campaign, even if it offers a chance for English football to rediscover itself. The last time the Premier League enjoyed an untroubled, uninterrupted 38-game season Raheem Sterling ended up being voted PFA young player of the year.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 19:00:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/the-premier-league-is-back-for-an-uncluttered-if-uncertain-new-season" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/09/anthony-joshua-random-drug-testing-boxing-dillian-whyte" target="_blank">Anthony Joshua calls for leading fighters to face random drug testing</a></h2><div class="description"> Anthony Joshua wants radical change to help tackle doping crisis. Joshua was meant to fight Dillian Whyte in London on Saturday night but his British rival has returned a positive test result for a still unnamed illegal substance. Whyte said he was “shocked and devastated” to learn of the test’s findings, while stating his innocence.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 19:00:33 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">health</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/09/anthony-joshua-random-drug-testing-boxing-dillian-whyte" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/sheffield-united-premier-league-2023-24-preview" target="_blank">Premier League 2023-24 preview No 17: Sheffield United</a></h2><div class="description"> Iliman Ndiaye is a massive blow to Paul Heckingbottom, who still has a large amount of players with Premier League experience. Daniel Jebbison will also look to youthful talent of Daniel Jebbison. The Championship side finished 2nd in the Championship last season.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 23:01:37 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/10/sheffield-united-premier-league-2023-24-preview" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/09/emma-finucane-sprints-to-gold-but-katie-archibald-misses-out" target="_blank">Heartache for Katie Archibald but Emma Finucane sprints to gold</a></h2><div class="description"> Scot fails to claim medal in the women's Omnium in the UCI Cycling World Championships. Katie Archibald admits pressure of competing in the velodrome had been overwhelming. Scot missed out on the medals in the Omnium after failing to claim a gold medal.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 20:56:06 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/09/emma-finucane-sprints-to-gold-but-katie-archibald-misses-out" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/carabao-cup-roundup-afc-wimbledon-stun-coventry-to-earn-trip-to-chelsea" target="_blank">Carabao Cup roundup: AFC Wimbledon stun Coventry to earn trip to Chelsea</a></h2><div class="description"> AFC Wimbledon beat Coventry 2-1 in their Carabao Cup clash. Fulham will play Tottenham in an all-Premier League tie in the week commencing 28 August. Leeds to face Salford after overcoming Shrewsbury. Wimbledon to face Chelsea in the second round of the competition.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 22:04:49 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/carabao-cup-roundup-afc-wimbledon-stun-coventry-to-earn-trip-to-chelsea" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/rangers-earn-slender-champions-league-advantage-after-beating-10-man-servette" target="_blank">Rangers earn slender Champions League advantage after beating 10-man Servette</a></h2><div class="description"> Rangers beat Servette 2-1 in Champions League third qualifying round first leg. Captain James Tavernier scored a penalty in the sixth minute. Cyriel Dessers scored his first goal for the club in the 15th minute. The Swiss side won the first leg at Ibrox in the second leg of the tie.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 20:58:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/09/rangers-earn-slender-champions-league-advantage-after-beating-10-man-servette" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/09/i-know-the-odds-celine-boutier-plays-down-chances-at-womens-open" target="_blank">‘I know the odds’: Céline Boutier plays down chances at Women’s Open</a></h2><div class="description"> Frenchwoman has won her past two outings, including a major, but realises history is against her making it three. The past 22 majors have produced 21 different champions - only Minjee Lee, at the 2021 Evian Championship and 2022 US Open, has doubled up during that time. Of those 21 players, 17 were first‑time major winners.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 16:18:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/09/i-know-the-odds-celine-boutier-plays-down-chances-at-womens-open" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/09/wembley-womens-challenge-cup-final-rugby-league-lois-forsell-leeds-st-helens" target="_blank">Wembley Challenge Cup final another giant step for women’s rugby league</a></h2><div class="description"> Women’s Challenge Cup final will take place at Wembley for the first time. Leeds Rhinos take on holders St Helens in a rematch of last year's decider. Leeds coach Lois Forsell: 'It's huge for future generations,’ says Forsell.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 13:23:35 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/aug/09/wembley-womens-challenge-cup-final-rugby-league-lois-forsell-leeds-st-helens" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/lula-brazil-amazon-rainforests-money" target="_blank">‘Nature needs money’: Lula tells rich countries to pay up and protect world’s rainforests</a></h2><div class="description"> Brazilian president says developed nations that over centuries have pumped emissions into the atmosphere must ‘pay their bit’ Major rainforest nations demand hundreds of billions of dollars of climate financing and a greater role in how those resources are spent. Lula: “It’s not Brazil that needs money. It's not Colombia or Venezuela,” Lula says.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:53:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/lula-brazil-amazon-rainforests-money" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/dam-partly-collapses-in-norway-as-storm-hans-continues-to-cause-chaos" target="_blank">Dam partly collapses in Norway as Storm Hans continues to cause chaos</a></h2><div class="description"> Parts of eastern and central Norway still on red alert as country battles widespread flooding and landslides. Police were considering blowing up the dam when water from the Glåma River, the country’s longest, started spilling out the side at Braskereidfoss hydroelectric power plant.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 16:32:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/dam-partly-collapses-in-norway-as-storm-hans-continues-to-cause-chaos" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/09/worlds-oldest-moss-could-go-extinct-as-a-result-of-climate-crisis" target="_blank">World’s oldest moss could go extinct as a result of climate crisis</a></h2><div class="description"> Takakia, 390m-year-old moss found in Himalayas, is at risk despite its ability to adapt to extreme weather. Takakia is one of the fastest-evolving species ever found, but that may not be enough to save it, scientists say.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 15:00:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/09/worlds-oldest-moss-could-go-extinct-as-a-result-of-climate-crisis" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/09/ai-helps-airline-pilots-avoid-areas-that-create-polluting-contrails" target="_blank">AI helps airline pilots avoid areas that create polluting contrails</a></h2><div class="description"> Experiment by Google and American Airlines reduces vapour trails, which are a source of global heating. Pilots flying using artificial intelligence models to choose different altitudes were able to reduce contrails by 54%. Further improvements are expected, Google said in a blogpost on Tuesday night.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:09:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/09/ai-helps-airline-pilots-avoid-areas-that-create-polluting-contrails" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/police-officers-in-northern-ireland-may-leave-force-or-move-after-data-breach-psni" target="_blank">Northern Ireland police data breach is second in weeks, force reveals</a></h2><div class="description"> Document with names of 200 staff was stolen in July, police admit. It follows revelation of ‘monumental’ data breach on Tuesday. Names of hundreds of officers and staff were leaked in July. Disclosures sowed anxiety in ranks and prompted some officers to relocate in case paramilitaries tried to exploit situation.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 18:11:42 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/police-officers-in-northern-ireland-may-leave-force-or-move-after-data-breach-psni" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/staffordshire-police-treating-fire-at-crooked-house-pub-as-arson" target="_blank">Staffordshire police treating fire at Crooked House pub as arson</a></h2><div class="description"> Blaze at famous pub nine days after it was sold to new owners sparked outrage and calls for it to be rebuilt. Police said they believed the fire ‘may have been started deliberately’ after fire investigators said the cause could “not currently be determined’.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 18:33:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/staffordshire-police-treating-fire-at-crooked-house-pub-as-arson" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/oxford-street-shoppers-locked-in-stores-amid-social-media-robbery-campaign" target="_blank">Police in Oxford Street make arrests amid social media ‘robbery campaign’</a></h2><div class="description"> Hundreds of teenagers gathered outside JD Sports in response to Snapchat call to take part in robbery. Police have arrested nine people and issued dozens of dispersal orders after shoppers were locked inside stores on London’s busiest shopping street. Shoppers were locked in stores after warnings of a robbery campaign organised on social media.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 20:00:47 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/oxford-street-shoppers-locked-in-stores-amid-social-media-robbery-campaign" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/09/hacked-uk-electoral-commission-data-target-voter-disinformation-warn-expert" target="_blank">Hacked UK voter data could be used to target disinformation, warn experts</a></h2><div class="description"> Data from Electoral Commission breach could allow rogue actors to create AI-generated messages in effort to manipulate elections. UK elections watchdog revealed on Tuesday that a hostile cyber-attack had been able to access the names and addresses of all voters registered between 2014 and 2022. State-backed actors could use the data to target voters with disinformation, experts have warned.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:21:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/09/hacked-uk-electoral-commission-data-target-voter-disinformation-warn-expert" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/09/yorkshire-council-warns-of-budget-crisis-as-deficit-reaches-47m" target="_blank">Yorkshire council warns of budget crisis as deficit reaches £47m</a></h2><div class="description"> Kirklees local authority, hit by underfunding, price rises and extra demand on services, reports precarious finances. Growing number of local authorities warn they are almost running out of funds. Kirklees council, which counts Huddersfield as its main town, said it could face a section 114 notice in the 2024/25 financial year.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 18:26:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/09/yorkshire-council-warns-of-budget-crisis-as-deficit-reaches-47m" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/09/four-of-britains-biggest-lenders-cut-rates-on-fixed-mortgage-deals" target="_blank">Four of Britain’s biggest lenders cut rates on fixed mortgage deals</a></h2><div class="description"> Halifax, HSBC, Nationwide and TSB reduce rates, easing pressure on hard-pressed homeowners. Halifax, part of Lloyds Banking Group – the UK’s biggest mortgage lender – is reducing rates by up to 0.71 percentage points from Friday. A five-year fixed rate currently priced at 6.10% will be offered at a rate of 5.39%.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 18:14:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/09/four-of-britains-biggest-lenders-cut-rates-on-fixed-mortgage-deals" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/hardeep-singh-kohli-comedian-charged-with-non-recent-sexual-offences" target="_blank">Comedian Hardeep Singh Kohli charged with non-recent sexual offences</a></h2><div class="description"> Scottish broadcaster arrested and released to appear in court at later date, say Police Scotland. Hardeep Singh Kohli charged in connection with non-recent sexual offences. Kohli, 54, has presented a number of programmes for the BBC, Channel 4, UKTV and other broadcasters.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 16:55:09 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/hardeep-singh-kohli-comedian-charged-with-non-recent-sexual-offences" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/jacqueline-mckenzie-conservative-hq-criticised-targeted-campaign-against-immigration-lawyer" target="_blank">Conservative HQ criticised for ‘targeted campaign’ against immigration lawyer</a></h2><div class="description"> Law Society and Bar Council ‘gravely concerned’ over briefing sent to right-leaning papers calling Jacqueline McKenzie a ‘lefty lawyer’ The head of immigration at Leigh Day said briefing was inaccurate and intended to whip up ill-feeling towards her.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 20:51:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2023/aug/09/jacqueline-mckenzie-conservative-hq-criticised-targeted-campaign-against-immigration-lawyer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/who-declares-eris-covid-strain-a-variant-of-interest-as-uk-cases-rise" target="_blank">WHO declares ‘Eris’ Covid strain a variant of interest as cases rise globally</a></h2><div class="description"> EG.5 or ‘Eris’ is related to an Omicron subvariant called XBB.1.9.2, and is growing in prevalence globally. UK, China and US among those affected. Public health risk judged to be low but may drive larger wave of infections.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 18:00:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">health</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/who-declares-eris-covid-strain-a-variant-of-interest-as-uk-cases-rise" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/09/welsh-secretary-has-history-of-hostility-towards-traveller-communities" target="_blank">Welsh secretary has ‘history of hostility’ towards Traveller communities</a></h2><div class="description"> Welsh secretary David TC Davies insisted he meant no criticism with a leaflet. Leaflet warned voters, “Gypsy and Traveller site coming to your area soon!” before asking them: “Would you like to see a Traveller. site next to your house?” Deputy Prime Minister Oliver Dowden defended Davies.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:46:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2023/aug/09/welsh-secretary-has-history-of-hostility-towards-traveller-communities" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/un-fears-niger-ex-president-running-out-food" target="_blank">US voices fears for Niger’s ex-president, who is ‘running out of food’</a></h2><div class="description"> Mohamed Bazoum, the West African nation’s democratically elected leader, has been held at the presidential palace in Niamey with his wife and son since July 26. His party said he and his family were running out of food and living under increasingly dire conditions.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 20:36:29 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/un-fears-niger-ex-president-running-out-food" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/kim-jong-un-fires-dismisses-north-korea-top-military-general-pak-su-il" target="_blank">Kim Jong-un fires North Korea’s top general and calls for weapons production boost</a></h2><div class="description"> Leader replaces Pak Su-il with defence minister, Gen Ri Yong-gil, and urges further military drills. Kim Jong-un calls for more preparations for possibility of war, boost in weapons production and expansion of drills. It remains unclear if Ri will retain his role as defence minister.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 00:42:10 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/10/kim-jong-un-fires-dismisses-north-korea-top-military-general-pak-su-il" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/argentina-election-campaigns-suspended-girl-killed-buenos-aires" target="_blank">Argentina election campaigns suspended after 11-year old killed in robbery</a></h2><div class="description"> Morena Domínguez was attacked by two robbers riding a motorcycle in Lanús, Buenos Aires. The 11-year-old was about to arrive at school early on Wednesday morning in the Buenos Aires district. The attackers snatched her mobile phone, and she fell to the pavement where she was left unconscious.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 21:25:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/argentina-election-campaigns-suspended-girl-killed-buenos-aires" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/mexico-president-amlo-gender-based-violence" target="_blank">Mexico: outrage as Amlo suggests critics guilty of ‘gender-based violence’ against him</a></h2><div class="description"> Comments touched a nerve in Mexico, where the government has been unable to tackle soaring levels of violence against women. A resurgent feminist movement has become a thorn in the president’s side. López Obrador's comments prompt condemnation in country with soaring level of violence.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 19:58:51 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/mexico-president-amlo-gender-based-violence" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/british-doctor-shot-and-killed-in-cape-town-amid-violent-taxi-strike-protests" target="_blank">British doctor shot and killed in Cape Town amid violent taxi strike protests</a></h2><div class="description"> The 40-year-old British national was with two family members when he drove into the city's Nyanga township. He encountered violent protests linked to a week-long taxi driver strike. The man, 40, took wrong turning from airport into township, where protests were taking place.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 18:06:27 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/british-doctor-shot-and-killed-in-cape-town-amid-violent-taxi-strike-protests" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/ohio-issue-1-abortion-rights-win" target="_blank">‘Ohio saw through the con’: abortion rights advocates celebrate Issue 1 result</a></h2><div class="description"> Ohio voters rejected Issue 1, a GOP-backed ballot measure that would have made it considerably harder to amend the state constitution. Issue 1 means Ohio keeps its longstanding rule on citizen-led state constitutional amendments: a simple majority of state voters can change the constitution through a ballot measure.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 19:53:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/ohio-issue-1-abortion-rights-win" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/mammoth-mountain-california-ski-season-ends" target="_blank">Ski season finally ends at California’s Mammoth Mountain resort</a></h2><div class="description"> The ski lifts at Mammoth Mountain, in the eastern Sierra Nevadas, have been open since early November and, up until 5 August, remained available well into summer. It was one of the longest seasons in resort’s 70-year history, helped out by a colossal snowpack from extreme winter weather.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 22:30:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/mammoth-mountain-california-ski-season-ends" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/worst-nightmare-south-korea-mulls-disastrous-scout-jamboree" target="_blank">‘Worst nightmare’: South Korea mulls disastrous Scout jamboree</a></h2><div class="description"> World Scout Jamboree in South Korea labelled a 'national disgrace' and a 'survival game' Concerns were raised before the event even began with flooding, flooded tents and sewage spills. South Korea has successfully hosted large events such as the Fifa World Cup and Winter Olympics.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 15:10:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/worst-nightmare-south-korea-mulls-disastrous-scout-jamboree" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/09/lizzo-sexual-harassment-complaints" target="_blank">Lawyers review at least six more complaints against Lizzo</a></h2><div class="description"> Attorney for three dancers who have accused singer says Los Angeles firm looking into further complaints. Los Angeles-based employment lawyer, Ron Zambrano, said the new allegations were of a ‘sexually charged environment” and failure to pay employees. Lizzo’s Watch Out for the Big Grrrls is based on her reality show.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 12:56:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/09/lizzo-sexual-harassment-complaints" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/biden-angers-climate-activists-emergency-statement" target="_blank">Climate activists outraged over Biden claim he ‘practically’ declared US emergency</a></h2><div class="description"> Biden said ‘I’ve already done that’ when asked about declaring climate emergency, yet White House has not announced such a declaration. Biden said he has ‘practically’ declared a national emergency on the climate crisis, despite not actually taking that step.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 19:55:41 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/09/biden-angers-climate-activists-emergency-statement" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/09/ben-target-lorenzo-review-summerhall-edinburgh" target="_blank">Ben Target: Lorenzo review – end-of-life care comedy is joyful and surprising</a></h2><div class="description"> Ben Target relives being a carer for a lovably eccentric adopted uncle in a heartfelt show that demonstrates caring’s reciprocal flow. The show flits between timelines to recount the relationship with Lorenzo, a fugitive from a rackety Hong Kong upbringing. Lorenzo was a maverick live-in colleague of his grandparents and “the only adult [Target] ever felt safe”</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 18:42:07 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/09/ben-target-lorenzo-review-summerhall-edinburgh" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/09/ladies-first-netflix-women-hip-hop-history-documentary" target="_blank">‘Women helped build this’: celebrating the ladies of hip-hop</a></h2><div class="description"> Ladies First: A Story of Women in Hip-Hop is a four-part docuseries on Netflix. It chronicles the trailblazing, underdog story of how women shaped the genre. It premieres to coincide with the 50th anniversary of the genre on 11 August.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:20:31 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/09/ladies-first-netflix-women-hip-hop-history-documentary" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/09/one-foot-in-the-grave-actor-doreen-mantle-dies-aged-97" target="_blank">One Foot in the Grave actor Doreen Mantle dies aged 97</a></h2><div class="description"> Mantle was best known for her performance as Jean Warboys, the annoying friend of Victor Meldrew’s wife, in the BBC comedy series One Foot in the Grave. The actor has died aged 97, her agent has announced. Mantle's agent confirmed that she had died at the age of 97.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 17:46:21 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2023/aug/09/one-foot-in-the-grave-actor-doreen-mantle-dies-aged-97" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/09/jamie-reid-artist-of-sex-pistols-record-covers-dies-aged-76" target="_blank">Jamie Reid, artist of Sex Pistols record covers, dies aged 76</a></h2><div class="description"> Artist and graphic designer’s cut-up work defined the iconoclastic energy of the punk era. Jamie leaves behind a beloved daughter Rowan, a granddaughter Rose, and an enormous legacy. He was described as an ‘iconoclast, anarchist, punk, hippie, rebel and romantic’</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 12:56:25 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/09/jamie-reid-artist-of-sex-pistols-record-covers-dies-aged-76" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/aug/09/billy-porter-house-actors-strike" target="_blank">‘You’ve starved me out’: Billy Porter says he’s lost his house to actors’ strike</a></h2><div class="description"> Pose star says ongoing strike has led him to sell his house. Porter also condemns Disney CEO for saying demands were 'unrealistic' The actors' union, Sag-Aftra, is currently on a month-long strike with the writers' strike, which has ground Hollywood to a halt.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 14:12:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/aug/09/billy-porter-house-actors-strike" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/09/elf-and-duffy-heist-review-comedy-monkey-barrel-at-the-tron-edinburgh" target="_blank">Elf and Duffy: Heist review – harum-scarum comedy havoc</a></h2><div class="description"> Monkey Barrel at the Tron, Edinburgh, is part-improvised, largely mimed and entirely chaotic comic play. Created with deaf artist Duffy, Heist is about guinea pigs and bank robbery. The show doesn't seem to know whether it’s scripted or improvised.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 11:49:32 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/aug/09/elf-and-duffy-heist-review-comedy-monkey-barrel-at-the-tron-edinburgh" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/gallery/2023/jun/07/from-pig-beach-to-dunns-river-falls-10-must-visit-caribbean-destinations-in-pictures" target="_blank">From Pig Beach to Dunn’s River Falls: 10 must-visit Caribbean destinations – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean is home to the world’s best beaches, pretty towns, waterfalls and national parks. There are stunning marine life, the best beaches and pretty towns in the world's most beautiful places. Here's the Caribbean in all its glory, including some pretty towns and waterfalls.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:35:34 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/gallery/2023/jun/07/from-pig-beach-to-dunns-river-falls-10-must-visit-caribbean-destinations-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/from-snorkelling-to-surfing-nine-must-try-caribbean-beach-and-water-activities" target="_blank">From snorkelling to surfing: nine must-try Caribbean beach and water activities</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean offers a huge variety of tempting activities from snorkelling to scuba diving. Windsurfing and waterskiing is a must-try activity for everyone. The Exu Exu is one of the Caribbean’s most beautiful, vividly coloured coral reefs.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:38:48 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/from-snorkelling-to-surfing-nine-must-try-caribbean-beach-and-water-activities" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/nightlife-loveseats-and-beautiful-beaches-why-the-caribbean-makes-for-the-perfect-romantic-holiday" target="_blank">Nightlife, loveseats and beautiful beaches: why the Caribbean makes for the perfect romantic holiday</a></h2><div class="description"> The Caribbean is an unbeatable destination for a romantic getaway with your loved one. From Jamaica to the hidden gem that is Curaçao, there’s something to suit every couple, whether on honeymoon, celebrating an anniversary, or just escaping everyday life for a taste of luxury.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:37:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/nightlife-loveseats-and-beautiful-beaches-why-the-caribbean-makes-for-the-perfect-romantic-holiday" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/waterfalls-history-and-the-worlds-first-underwater-sculpture-park-seven-exciting-things-to-do-in-the-caribbean" target="_blank">Waterfalls, history and the world’s first underwater sculpture park: seven exciting things to do in the Caribbean</a></h2><div class="description"> The islands of the Caribbean are like nowhere else on Earth. From cocktails to coral reefs, they offer something for all tastes and tempos. Enjoy a classic mojito or piña colada on the white sand beaches of Barbados or Jamaica. Explore the area’s rich history and natural beauty.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 10:36:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/discover-the-best-of-the-caribbean/2023/jun/07/waterfalls-history-and-the-worlds-first-underwater-sculpture-park-seven-exciting-things-to-do-in-the-caribbean" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/a-moment-that-changed-me-i-was-outraged-by-the-risks-facing-my-children-so-we-moved-to-the-country" target="_blank">A moment that changed me: I was outraged by the risks facing my children - so we moved to the country</a></h2><div class="description"> Black Caribbean people born in the UK have a higher chance of schizophrenia, and city life is a factor. So when a chance came to live in Somerset, I leapt at it. The life expectancy for any person diagnosed with a psychotic illness was 15 years shorter than the UK average.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 06:00:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/a-moment-that-changed-me-i-was-outraged-by-the-risks-facing-my-children-so-we-moved-to-the-country" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/3967-steps-a-day-the-new-magic-number-for-a-healthy-happy-life" target="_blank">3,967 steps a day: the new magic number for a healthy, happy life?</a></h2><div class="description"> The very thought of exercise can be tiring, but don't despair. Small changes can make a big difference to your body. Walking has been around 300m to 400m years since our ancestors replaced fins and gills with legs. It is thought that our ancestors have been walking for 300m years.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 14:05:18 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/09/3967-steps-a-day-the-new-magic-number-for-a-healthy-happy-life" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/09/how-to-make-the-perfect-vegan-moussaka-recipe-felicity-cloake" target="_blank">How to make the perfect vegan moussaka – recipe | Felicity Cloake's How to make the perfect ...</a></h2><div class="description"> Our in-house perfectionist scours Greece and the Levant for the best of the best vegan versions of this much-loved layer bake. Even in Greece, the 200-odd fasting days a year mandated by the Orthodox church mean that plant-based cuisine is more common than the casual visitor surviving on souvlaki and sea bass.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 11:00:23 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2023/aug/09/how-to-make-the-perfect-vegan-moussaka-recipe-felicity-cloake" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/09/hmrc-froze-my-daughters-tax-free-childcare-account" target="_blank">After an HMRC error, my daughter’s childcare cash was frozen</a></h2><div class="description"> A payment of £779 into my daughter’s account was credited five times. Five months on, I still can’t get the cash to pay her nursery fees. More than 8,000 families were locked out of their accounts in February when deposits were erroneously multiplied by the banking provider used by NS&I.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 06:00:06 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/09/hmrc-froze-my-daughters-tax-free-childcare-account" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/tiktok-how-shopping-went-social-hooked-new-generation" target="_blank">‘Where did I get my top? TikTok!’ How shopping went social – and hooked a new generation</a></h2><div class="description"> Zainab Hakim, 23, watches sellers livestream on TikTok, peddling their wares in real time. With a couple of clicks, she can buy things via the app via TikTok Live. Hakim bought eight items from eight sellers in just one afternoon.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 13:00:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/aug/08/tiktok-how-shopping-went-social-hooked-new-generation" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/13/why-barcelonas-beaches-are-disappearing-video" target="_blank">Why Barcelona’s beaches are disappearing – video</a></h2><div class="description"> In 2010, Barcelona’s nine city beaches were topped up with 700,000 cubic metres of sand. Since then, 70% of that sand has disappeared. In the past 20 years the rate of erosion along Spain's east coast has been accelerating. It is partly to do with storms and rising sea levels but there are other factors at play.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 13 Jul 2023 08:46:44 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/13/why-barcelonas-beaches-are-disappearing-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">What you need to know about the 'extreme' heatwave hitting our oceans – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> Sea temperatures, particularly off the north-east coast of England and west of Ireland, are several degrees above normal, breaking records for late spring and early summer. The Met Office has said that according to records dating to 1850, global sea surface temperatures in April and May reached an all-time high.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 22 Jun 2023 14:22:05 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jun/22/what-you-need-to-know-about-the-extreme-heatwave-hitting-our-oceans-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">I was a terrorist. Now I run a kindergarten – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Hendi Suhartono was part of a plot to detonate four book bombs and blow up a church in Indonesia. He spent seven years in prison after going through a deradicalisation process. After being released from prison, he received support to open a kindergarten.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 25 Jul 2023 09:15:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/video/2023/jul/25/i-was-a-terrorist-now-i-run-a-kindergarten-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Inside the NHS as staff say future hangs in the balance – video</a></h2><div class="description"> The NHS was launched in 1948 by Labour MP Aneurin Bevan, inspired in part by the Tredegar Medical Aid Society in his constituency. It has since saved millions of lives and inspired health systems around the world. Seventy-five years on, the Guardian video team was given access to NHS services in south Wales town.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 10:19:40 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/video/2023/jul/04/nhs-founder-would-turn-in-his-grave-as-service-faces-crisis-at-75-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">What is supercharging the global heat? – video explainer</a></h2><div class="description"> The planet is being hit with a double whammy of global heating in 2023: on top of the rise in global temperature caused by greenhouse gas emissions is an emerging El Niño. This sporadic event is the biggest natural influence on year-to-year weather and adds a further spurt of warmth to an already overheating world.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 16:48:08 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/19/what-is-supercharging-the-global-heat-video-explainer" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">How I survived a 'sex-ed shitstorm' – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Cartoonist Fiona Katauskas's book, The Amazing True Story of How Babies are Made, had been on Kmart and Big W shelves for three years. What started as a debate over the offending picture on Facebook would explode over several days into multiple headlines. Here is her take on what happened.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Thu, 27 Jul 2023 15:00:43 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/education/video/2023/jul/28/how-i-survived-a-sex-ed-shitstorm-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Kids v cars: the campaign to reclaim children's play space on British streets – video</a></h2><div class="description"> Playing Out is helping to close streets to cars to reclaim the space on children’s doorsteps. Some experts say a growing mental and physical health crisis could be a result. Families are campaigning for children to have fun outdoors again. The Guardian's Harriet Grant travels to Bristol to meet Playing Out.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 11 Jul 2023 09:30:38 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/video/2023/jul/11/kids-vs-cars-taking-back-play-space-on-british-streets-video" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/09/tell-us-whats-your-experience-with-buy-now-pay-later-schemes-in-the-uk" target="_blank">Tell us: what’s your experience with buy now, pay later schemes in the UK?</a></h2><div class="description"> Buy no, pay later schemes like Klarna and Clearpay have surged in recent years. People in the UK spent £5.6bn in the first six months of 2022 alone. 49% of people of those with a BNPL loan find it difficult to keep up with household bills.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 16:16:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/09/tell-us-whats-your-experience-with-buy-now-pay-later-schemes-in-the-uk" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/08/uk-workers-are-you-struggling-to-get-the-hours-youd-like-to-work" target="_blank">UK workers: are you struggling to get the hours you’d like to work?</a></h2><div class="description"> We want to hear from ‘underemployed’ workers who are not getting as much work as they’d like. Whether you’ve had trouble finding full time work, have had shifts cancelled regularly or have had your hours reduced permanently by your employer since you signed up for the job.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 13:27:23 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/money/2023/aug/08/uk-workers-are-you-struggling-to-get-the-hours-youd-like-to-work" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/09/share-your-experience-of-travelling-outside-the-uk-for-ivf" target="_blank">Share your experience of travelling outside the UK for IVF</a></h2><div class="description"> People in the UK are increasingly funding IVF treatments privately, research shows. 63% of IVF funded privately in 2021 compared to 52% in 2019. IVF cycles funded by the NHS saw a decrease to 20,000 in 2021 from around 24,000. We want to hear from people who have travelled abroad for fertility treatments.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 12:05:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/society/2023/aug/09/share-your-experience-of-travelling-outside-the-uk-for-ivf" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/09/why-the-rest-of-the-world-cant-afford-to-ignore-the-coup-in-niger-podcast" target="_blank">Why the rest of the world can’t afford to ignore the coup in Niger – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> The Sahel region, sometimes called Africa’s ‘coup belt’ has just seen another government ousted. The eighth overthrow of a government in the region in the past three years and may be the most significant. Peter Beaumont and Nesrine Malik on what it means for African – and global – security.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 02:00:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/09/why-the-rest-of-the-world-cant-afford-to-ignore-the-coup-in-niger-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/08/colombia-set-up-quarter-final-with-england-womens-football-weekly-podcast" target="_blank">Colombia set up quarter-final with England – Women’s Football Weekly</a></h2><div class="description"> Colombia beat Jamaica 1-0 to reach their first ever quarter-final, where they will face England. Faye Carruthers is joined by Suzy Wrack, Sophie Downey and Jonathan Liew as the round of 16 comes to a close. We also bid farewell to the Reggae Girlz, who became the first Caribbean nation to play in knockout stages of a World Cup, male or female, since Cuba in 1938.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 15:47:13 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/08/colombia-set-up-quarter-final-with-england-womens-football-weekly-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/audio/2023/aug/08/summer-picks-should-we-ban-artificial-grass-podcast" target="_blank">Summer picks: should we ban artificial grass? – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Madeleine Finlay speaks to Guardian feature writer Sam Wollaston and urban ecologist Prof Rob Francis about why people go for artificial grass. She also discusses whether it's time to rid ourselves of the idea of the perfect lawn altogether. In April 2023, 2023 will feature an interview with Prof Francis and a panel of experts on artificial lawns.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 04:00:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/science/audio/2023/aug/08/summer-picks-should-we-ban-artificial-grass-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/08/the-legacy-of-sinead-oconnor-podcast" target="_blank">The legacy of Sinéad O’Connor – podcast</a></h2><div class="description"> Kathryn Ferguson and journalist Simon Hattenstone share their memories of Sinéad O'Connor. Ferguson directed Nothing Compares, a 2022 documentary about the singer's life. She explains why O’Connor spoke out about abuse in the Catholic church in the early 1990s when it was still taboo to do so.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 02:00:00 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/audio/2023/aug/08/the-legacy-of-sinead-oconnor-podcast" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/07/world-cup-england-nigeria-australia-denmark" target="_blank">Women’s Football Weekly: Lionesses find a way to win after James red card</a></h2><div class="description"> Faye Carruthers, Suzanne Wrack, Ceylon Andi Hickman and Tim Stillman discuss an eventful three days of last-16 Women’s World Cup action. There was drama in Brisbane as the Lionesses scraped through to the quarter-finals. But what next for Lauren James? After dazzling in the group, the starlet faces a spell on the sidelines following her sending off.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 20:01:52 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">sports</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/football/audio/2023/aug/07/world-cup-england-nigeria-australia-denmark" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/09/apple-maps-cycling-transport-google" target="_blank">A decade after a disastrous launch, is Apple Maps finally good?</a></h2><div class="description"> Engineers’ work on cycling and public transit have transformed the app – but rural directions remain a sticking point. In October 2022, New York City officials unveiled a new bike lane on Schermerhorn street, one of the most dangerous and heavily trafficked streets in downtown Brooklyn. For Apple to know the lane was open, it had to have updates from the Adams administration.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 10:00:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">tech</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2023/aug/09/apple-maps-cycling-transport-google" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/09/people-would-have-lost-their-culture-the-birmingham-record-label-that-saved-south-asian-music" target="_blank">‘People would have lost their culture’: the Birmingham record label that saved south Asian music</a></h2><div class="description"> Muhammad Ayyub moved to Birmingham from Pakistan from Gujrat in 1961. The 84-year-old opened a shop selling transistor radios on Balsall Heath Road in 1966. Oriental Star Agencies championed legends such as Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan and nurtured bhangra.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 14:05:24 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/aug/09/people-would-have-lost-their-culture-the-birmingham-record-label-that-saved-south-asian-music" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/10/even-closing-my-eyes-is-an-intense-movement-the-vr-experience-that-simulates-a-serious-neurological-condition" target="_blank">‘Even closing my eyes is an intense movement’: the VR experience that simulates a serious neurological condition</a></h2><div class="description"> Ben Joseph Andrews’ chronic vestibular condition leaves him with migraines and dizziness – which he has transformed into a VR experience. Luke Buckmaster gives it a taste of a 'world-first mixed reality' experience at this year’s Melbourne international film festival.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 15:00:28 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/aug/10/even-closing-my-eyes-is-an-intense-movement-the-vr-experience-that-simulates-a-serious-neurological-condition" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/law/2023/aug/09/leonard-leo-federalist-society-manipulates-free-speech" target="_blank">How a Trump adviser manipulates free speech to advance his causes and ‘hurt his adversaries’</a></h2><div class="description"> Leonard Leo, architect of the rightwing takeover of the US judiciary, champions the first amendment for political gain but does an ‘about-face’ when it’s used against him, critics say. Leo, 58, is the low-profile, deceptively nondescript co-chair of the conservative legal group Federalist Society.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 11:00:24 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/law/2023/aug/09/leonard-leo-federalist-society-manipulates-free-speech" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/09/uk-is-ill-equipped-to-protect-workers-against-pitfalls-of-ai" target="_blank">UK is ill-equipped to protect workers against pitfalls of AI</a></h2><div class="description"> Rishi Sunak will gather world leaders in London this autumn for a summit on safety in artificial intelligence. Culture, media and sport select committee has warned of risks not just to workers’ jobs but also their autonomy. The committee has expressed concern about the “existential risks” of the rapidly evolving technology.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 05:00:04 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/aug/09/uk-is-ill-equipped-to-protect-workers-against-pitfalls-of-ai" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/new-orleans-archdiocese-clerical-sex-abuse-claims" target="_blank">300 New Orleans priests were reported for sexual abuse – only 25% are on archdiocese’s ‘credibly accused’ list</a></h2><div class="description"> The number of accused – 310, spanning several decades – has been kept from public as archdiocese undergoes bankruptcy proceedings. New Orleans archbishop has spent significant portion of recent history managing the fallout from its association with the worldwide Catholic church's clerical molestation scandal. The organization has generally sought to keep hidden the exact number of priests, deacons, nuns, religious brothers and lay staffers.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 10:00:22 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/09/new-orleans-archdiocese-clerical-sex-abuse-claims" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2022/sep/20/sign-up-for-the-fashion-statement-newsletter-our-free-fashion-email" target="_blank">Sign up for the Fashion Statement newsletter: our free fashion email</a></h2><div class="description"> Style, with substance: what’s really trending this week, a roundup of the best fashion journalism and your wardrobe dilemmas solved, delivered straight to your inbox every Thursday. Find out what's really trending and what you need to look at this week's top fashion stories.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 20 Sep 2022 11:06:20 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global/2022/sep/20/sign-up-for-the-fashion-statement-newsletter-our-free-fashion-email" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2019/jul/09/sign-up-for-word-of-mouth-the-best-of-guardian-food-every-week" target="_blank">Sign up for Word of Mouth: the best of Guardian Food every week</a></h2><div class="description"> A weekly email bringing you our best food writing, the latest recipes, seasonal eating ideas and must-read restaurant reviews. Sign up below to start receiving the best of our culinary journalism in one mouth-watering weekly email. We'll send you latest recipes from Yotam Ottolenghi, Nigel Slater, Meera Sodha and all our star cooks.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 09 Jul 2019 08:19:21 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">health</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/food/2019/jul/09/sign-up-for-word-of-mouth-the-best-of-guardian-food-every-week" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/gallery/2023/aug/09/frankfurt-flyers-and-a-hot-dog-wednesdays-best-photos" target="_blank">A Frankfurt flock and a hot dog: Wednesday’s best photos</a></h2><div class="description"> The Guardian’s picture editors select photo highlights from around the world. The Guardian's photo highlights are selected by the Guardian's picture editors each week to highlight the best of the day. In the world's top 10 photos, please submit your best for next week's top ten.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 12:05:15 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/news/gallery/2023/aug/09/frankfurt-flyers-and-a-hot-dog-wednesdays-best-photos" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/gallery/2023/aug/09/saul-leiter-photos-paintings-in-pictures" target="_blank">‘There’s nothing quite like them’: Saul Leiter’s photos and paintings – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> The iconic photographer considered himself a painter before anything else – and a new exhibition shows his colourful, abstract work alongside his photography. A new exhibition of his abstract work will also be held in London, London, at the end of November. The exhibition will run until December 31, 2015.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Wed, 09 Aug 2023 06:00:06 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/gallery/2023/aug/09/saul-leiter-photos-paintings-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/gallery/2023/aug/08/the-women-calling-for-reform-of-venezuelas-severe-anti-abortion-laws-in-pictures" target="_blank">The women calling for reform of Venezuela’s severe anti-abortion laws – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> Century-old legislation in the South American country decrees up to six years in prison for those who have or provide abortions. Despite demands for change, the government shows no sign of reforming the 1926 law. Only in 2000 was it amended to allow for abortions to save the life of the pregnant woman.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 07:00:03 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">world</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/gallery/2023/aug/08/the-women-calling-for-reform-of-venezuelas-severe-anti-abortion-laws-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/gallery/2023/aug/08/difference-is-beautiful-pregnant-trans-men-go-for-a-swim-in-pictures" target="_blank">‘Difference is beautiful’: pregnant trans men go for a swim – in pictures</a></h2><div class="description"> Seahorse Parents is a photography and film project in which four soon-to-be parents share their personal stories of what carrying future children as transgender men has been like. The project aims to document the experience of carrying future transgender children as a transgender man as a parent.</div><br><span class="date"><strong>Published on:</strong> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 06:00:02 GMT</span><br><div class="category"><strong>Category: </strong><span class="category-text">entertainment</span></div><br><div class="source"><strong>Source: </strong><span class="source-text">The Guardian</span></div><br><div class="link"><a href="https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/gallery/2023/aug/08/difference-is-beautiful-pregnant-trans-men-go-for-a-swim-in-pictures" target="_blank">Click here to read the full article</a></div><br></div><hr><div class='item'><h2><a href="https://www.standard.co.uk/news/uk/rishi-sunak-britain-the-times-met-daily-express-b10